ElementDescription: Social and Occupational Functioning Assessment Scale (SOFAS) Code
Notes: 0=Inadequate information; 10=Persistent inability to maintain minimal personal hygiene, unable to function without harming self or others or without considerable external support, such as nursing care and supervision; 20=Occasionally fails to maintain minimal personal hygiene, unable to function independently; 30=Inability to function in almost all areas, e.g., stays in bed all day, no job, home, or friends; 40=Major impairment in several areas, such as work or school, family relations, e.g., depressed man avoids friends, neglects family, and is unable to work, child frequently beats up younger children, is defiant at home, and is failing at school; 50=Serious impairment in social, occupational, or school functioning, e.g., no friends, unable to keep a job; 60=Moderate difficulty in social, occupational, or school functioning, e.g., few friends, conflicts with peers or coworkers; 70=Some difficulty in social, occupational, or school functioning, but generally functioning well, has some meaningful interpersonal relationships; 80=No more than a slight impairment in social, occupational, or school functioning, e.g., infrequent interpersonal conflict, temporarily falling behind in schoolwork; 90=Good functioning in all areas, occupationally and socially effective; 100=Superior functioning in a wide range of activities
